abstract: "Code and data for the first base-vs-instruct comparison of scoring bias in LLM-as-a-Judge. Tests 44 model families (88 variants) across 3 scoring bias probes totaling 118,800 judgments. Finds that instruction tuning has differential effects: format biases decrease by 44-77% while content bias increases by 35%."
